summary: Pre-installed package unchanged when best=True in dnf.conf
description: |
  System repo: foo-1.4, bar (baseline)
  Pre-installed: foo-1.0 (lower than system version)
  Artifacts: None
  dnf.conf: best=True (simulates RHEL/CentOS defaults)

  When a missing package (bar) forces dnf install to run for the full set,
  the already-installed foo must not be upgraded even with best=True.
  Fix must not rely on the distro's best= default.

context+:
  xfail: "true"

environment+:
  BEST_ENABLED: "True"
  PRE_INSTALLED_PACKAGE: rpms/foo-1.0/foo-1.0*.rpm
  EXPECTED_PACKAGE: foo-1.0

/with-bar:
  summary+: " (foo and bar requested, bar missing)"
  context+:
    with_bar: "true"
  environment+:
    SYSTEM_PACKAGE+: " bar"
